        <h2>Course Description</h2>
        <p>The Newlands Clinic Research Masterclass is a 12-week online program designed to introduce medical doctors to the fundamentals of clinical research, epidemiology, and scientific writing. Based at Newlands Clinic, this course empowers clinicians to transition from consuming medical literature to actively contributing to it.</p>
        <p>The program teaches professionals how to design robust studies, analyze epidemiological data, and synthesize their findings into publication-ready manuscripts. Participants will apply their knowledge through structured weekly sessions and targeted readings, demonstrating real-world research capabilities relevant to their clinical practice.</p>

        <h2>Bootcamp Features</h2>
        <ul class="features-grid">
            <li>A 3-Month Guided Course</li>
            <li>Weekly live 1-hour lectures</li>
            <li>Targeted weekly independent reading (2 hours)</li>
            <li>Real-world clinical examples and datasets</li>
            <li>Personalized feedback on writing assignments</li>
            <li>Shareable certificate upon completion</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Workload and Recommended Credits</h2>
        <p>The 12-week course comprises weekly lectures and independent learning, totaling approximately 36 hours of work. A detailed breakdown of the course workload is shown below.</p>
        
